Brazilian Stock Movers: Eletropaulo, JBS, MMX Mineracao, MRV

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-03-24T14:22:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/brazilian-stock-movers-eletropaulo-jbs-mmx-mineracao-mrv.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:15 a.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 0.4 percent to 67,525.19.  Eletropaulo Metropolitana SA (ELPL4 BS) gained 1.6 percent
to 34.95 reais. The Brazilian unit of AES Corp. reported fourth-
quarter net income of 299.7 million reais ($180.8 million).  JBS SA (JBSS3)  (JBSS3 BS) lost 2.3 percent to 5.90 reais. The
world’s biggest beef producer posted a net loss of 499.5 million
reais in the fourth quarter.  MMX Mineracao & Metalicos SA (MMXM3 BS) gained 1.7 percent
to 9.46 reais. The iron-ore producer controlled by billionaire
 Eike Batista  said fourth-quarter net income was 83.8 million
reais, according to a regulatory filing today.  MRV Engenharia & Participacoes SA (MRVE3 BS) tumbled 5.2
percent to 13.37 reais.  Brazil ’s fifth-biggest homebuilder by
revenue posted fourth-quarter net income of 152.1 million reais.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in Sao Paulo at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  